title: UVA Rotunda. Spring Afternoon
description: My inspiration for this sunny afternoon painting occurred following a stroll “on the Lawn” after the final UVA men’s basketball game of the 2020 season.

title: Yellowstone Afternoon Hike
description: While hiking Hell Roaring Creek Trail August 2020, I captured the beauty of a summer afternoon on film while hearing this roaring creek which feeds into the Yellowstone River. I was not only inspired to paint it recently but to go back and hike it again!

title: Tidal Basin Cherry Blossoms
description: Each year I walk the Tidal Basin during cherry blossom season and receive this visual inspiration for future paintings. Here is my most recent painting done during COVID when I used memories to inspire!!!

title: Bass Lighthouse, Maine
description: Visit Bar Harbor, Maine and Acadia National Park. Catch the sunset seen here over Bar Harbor Lighthouse!

title: Sedona Sunrise
description: Morning hikes in Arizona State Parks near Sedona reveal peace and wonder. Often you are surrounded by vortexes. If time allows, sit, relax and breath in the beauty of a morning sunrise. Life changing!

title: Sedona afternoon
description: Vortices abound along this hiking path near Sedona, Arizona. Relax and take in the beauty and tranquility of the rolling creek and desert breeze.

title: Amalfi City Beach
description: Visit the Amalfi Coast of Italy and live the dream of a family holiday like no other. This trip was my painting inspiration!

title: Bighorn National Forest
description: This early morning scene was painted in vibrant colors and depicted morning, southwest light.

title: Longhorn in Sage
description: While walking along the Rio Grande, I saw a herd of Longhorns near this bridge, and photographed many of them. This picture emphasizes the strength of this animal, as well as the Golden Hour sunlight.

title: New Zealand Port
description: This sunny afternoon coastal scene occurred on the South Island of New Zealand. My daughter and I enjoyed walking by the beach and later, eating fresh seafood. It will long be remembered.

title: Niece and Nephew
description: My niece took pictures of my grandniece and grandnephew in front of a neighbor’s sunflower field. After receiving this photo, I was inspired to paint it.

title: Paris
description: While walking along the Seine River on a Winter day, I anxiously awaited my tour of the Louvre and took these pictures for painting.

title: Bison in Hayden Valley
description: I viewed these two bison by the banks of the Lamar River in Yellowstone National Park.

title: Condensation Lamp
description: A fused glass lamp fired multiple times in a kiln utilizing clear glass and copper oxide to give it a blue color and bubbles.

title: Statement lamp
description: This is a fused glass lampshade artfully designing chips and pieces of glass that is definitely an attention getter.

title: Nightlight
description: An aqua and lime green fused glass nightlight utilizing chips of glass called frit and lightly fused to a clear base that makes a perfect nightlight

title: Sunflower candleholder
description: A fused glass sunflower candleholder. Each piece of glass is handcut, ground and fused multiple times in a kiln.

title: Candleholder
description: A fused glass candleholder handcutting glass and using chips of glass called “frit” for interest.

title: Blue, green glass splash art
description: Fused glass wall art that I call “glass splashing”. It is quickly fired in a kiln that twists and turns the glass. I then take each individual splash and artfully arrange and then fuse it one last time in the kiln.

title: Deep Sea
description: A lightly fused wall art piece that can be sold as a set or individually. Each piece utilizes blue and turquoise glass artfully arranged and fired to give it depth and represent the deep sea.

title: Sunflower heart pendant
description: A fused glass heart that can either be an ornament or worn as a pendant. It uses murrini and blue and green glass to give it a field of flowers appearance.

title: Blue Chevron Dichroic Pendant
description: A sample of fused glass dichroic pendants.

title: Fused glass orange dichroic pendant
description: A sample of fused glass dichroic pendants where a natural hole was made when the pendant was firing to serve as a bail for a chain.

title: Fused Glass hand painted dishes
description: The painting in each dish is placed between two pieces of glass, fired and sealed in to the glass giving it a floating appearance and making it food safe and dishwasher safe.

title: Fused Glass Donut Hole Lamp
description: A fused glass lamp called “Donut Holes” as the glass circles are from what is left from previous lamps after drilling a hole to allow the shade to attach to the base.

title: Fused Glass lampshade
description: A fused glass lampshade fusing to different pieces of glass together (green and wispy clear) and then adding decorative elements of glass vitrigraph and frit and firing it several more times to give it a final handkerchief drape look.

title: Glass Splash Art - Red
description: This fused glass wall art was made firing glass frit to a high temperature that give each a unique shape. I then design each piece and lightly fuse them for their finished look.

title: Fused Glass Splash Art - Red
description: This fused glass wall art was made firing glass frit to a high temperature that give each a unique shape. I then design each piece and lightly fuse them for their finished look.

title: And Yet the Meadowlark Sings
description: I love the sound of the Meadowlark. As their habitats disappear, I see and hear them less and less. I still get a thrill when I see one!

title: Holy Goat!
description: This is another joyful farm friend that I met during the Loudoun County Farm Tour last year!

title: Farm Girl’s Tree
description: This view gives me a wistful feeling, like when I was a young girl visiting the farm of an old relative. On this misty morning, the tree swing awaited....

title: Burrowing Owl and Moon
description: This intensely-staring burrowing owl is part of my “Owl and Moon” Series. These paintings appear different depending on the light in the room and time of day. I use metal leaf to make the moon glow, and I love the juxtaposition of the pastel pigment with the metal.

title: Autumn Dune
description: This painting depicts sunrise at one of my favorite places on the earth...Coquina Beach in the Outer Banks of NC. The sky, sea, and dunes change colors every hour, every day, every season.

title: Greenhill Guardian
description: If you’ve ever peeked over the hill when traveling towards Middleburg on Route 50, you’ve seen this magnificent sycamore tree which towers over the vineyard.

title: Better off Here Than Across the Street
description: A nocturnal streetscape from our beautiful town, Leesburg, VA!

title: Wren Royalty
description: I love wrens. This humble house wren is rightly elevated in importance with the gold background.

title: Glowing Gobbler
description: This magnificent tom turkey lives at Temple Hall Farm north of Leesburg. His impressive feathers, in sunlight, almost looked like tissue paper!

title: Julie’s Chickens
description: These are my sister’s chickens, running around her yard on a cold early winter morning.

title: Great-Horned Owl and Moon
description: This beautiful girl is part of my “Owl and Moon Series”. I love the juxtaposition of the glowing moon with the pastel pigment.

title: Seagull Liftoff
description: I know some people call these resilient and tenacious birds “sky trash”, but I love to watch them, and the beach wouldn’t be the same without them.

title: Red Beauty
description: I love birds. Cardinals seems to have a significant presence for many people.

title: Backlit Swan
description: Swans appear graceful in every action. I used metal leaf to make the water shimmer behind this backlit swan.

title: Mona Lisa (after Leonardo da Vinci)
description: It is good for artists to copy the work of the Masters. This one took me two years, and I learned so much!

title: Stump Planter

description: This planter has a hole for drainage and handles to encourage the gardener to bring the planter inside for the winter. The surface has a bark like texture with an applied Tenmoku glaze.

title: Firing the Wood Kiln (Final Salt)
description: After 36 hours of hand feeding wood into the kiln we input salt into the fire. The salt melts and then vaporizes, breaking down to sodium and chloride. This process melts the silica on the unglazed surfaces of the pot forming a glaze with a texture that resembles an orange peel.

title: Slave fragment
description: I sculpt the original figure, a plaster mold is made on the original sculpture. Slabs of textured clay with brick, lath ,gears or what ever are torn and pressed in layers into the figure mold, so that each torso is different. They are multiple originals within a Limited edition of that figure form.

title: Spirit of Learning

title: Stanley Caulkins

title: Reaching for the future
description: Two kids, one girl and one African American boy reaching for the future, the world. Representing a style of teaching. Installed at the Capitol Hill Montessori school in Washington DC

title: I’ll Fly Away
description: This is one in a series of paintings inspired by the Bluegrass music of my childhood here in Virginia. “I’ll Fly Away” is a traditional gospel song that is a favorite at family gatherings, jam sessions and in worship services. It’s joyful message is one of hope for a better world to come.

title: Moonscape
description: Moonscape is a tribute to my childhood memories of my father who introduced me to viewing the full moon with a powerful telescope.

title: Attraction
description: Attraction is an abstract representation of the idea of attraction.

title: Heart in Hand
description: The hand is represented in many cultures, the heart denotes the idea of friendship and love.

title: Razzmatazz
description: Razzmatazz is an abstract metal sculpture composed of large, discarded metal fragments from the steel industry.

title: Vertical Vision
description: Vertical Vision is a welded steel sculpture composed of three bent tubes with steel form additions, attached to the main body of the sculpture.

title: Sentinel
description: Sentinel is a guardian welded steel sculpture.

title: Celebration
description: Celebration was a difficult sculpture to create. The woven steel rebar was heated to orange heat and folded over itself to create the enigmatic object.

title: Sculptural Table
